Nigerian music star Keziah Jones is slated to stage his debut performance in Nairobi at the second edition of the Cool Waters Jazz &amp; Roots Festival scheduled for September 22 24, 2016. The singer and multi-instrumentalist will join music icons Franck Biyong from Cameroon and Botswana s Kabo Leburu for the boutique festival that will be held in multiple venues around Nairobi.Keziah, 48, describes his musical style as "Blufunk", a fusion between raw blues elements and hard, edgy funk rhythms.The three-day affair which promises to be an eclectic and invigorating musical experience will also feature performances from Achien g Abura, Eddie Grey, Tetu Tutuma and Maia von Lekow whose latest single, Lola, is currently stirring waves across the Kenyan live music scene. This initiative seeks to enable music lovers to discover new voices, celebrate seasoned talent and explore unique sounds as we celebrate the values of culture, innovation and improvisation that Jazz and Roots music offers the world, said Roots International's Abdi Rashid Jibril. This year our plan is to bring a distinct music aesthetic that will enrich audience members and leave a lasting impression on the vibrant community of local and international music lovers in Nairobi, he adds. This will be the first time the event will happen in more than one venue since the festival premiered on the city s live music circuit in September 2015. The 2016 series will be held at Choices Pub &amp; Restaurant on September 22, Tree House Museum Hill (September 23) and The Elephant (September 24). Advance Tickets are available at select Java Coffee House outlets and via Safaricom Paybill number 701924.